<denchmark-link:https://github.com/Whisht>@Whisht</denchmark-link> It is strange. I know you are trying to access tutorials page. Tutorials page should look like this <denchmark-link:https://screenshot.googleplex.com/DMWAtBAQvkx>https://screenshot.googleplex.com/DMWAtBAQvkx</denchmark-link>
Could you tell from which region (Asia, Europe, America etc) your are accessing TF website? Are you using Chrome? Could you check the same page using others (IE,Firefox, Safari etc) Do you see similar things in other pages. Could you share a screenshot. Thanks!

<denchmark-link:https://github.com/jvishnuvardhan>@jvishnuvardhan</denchmark-link>
Absolutely.
I access tensorflow.org from China. Yes, the browser is Chrome. And this page display the same error no matter browser I use. The same error is happened in https://developers.google.com/ and any sub-page of tensorflow.org. Here are the screenshots.
<denchmark-link:https://github.com/Whisht>@Whisht</denchmark-link> Does this happen when you access the site through tensorflow.google.cn ? Do you have any JavaScript blockers on?

<denchmark-link:https://github.com/lamberta>@lamberta</denchmark-link> No matter tensorflow.google.cn or tensorflow.org, I encountered the same error. And I have turned the blockers off. For that I did't misjudge, I have tried to access these website through other browsers, such as Firefox and Microsoft Edge which have no type of plug-ins.
This seems related to how webfonts from fonts.googleapis.com are blocked in China. Tracking: b/134091451
Hi <denchmark-link:https://github.com/Whisht>@Whisht</denchmark-link> , can you try this again? Testing thinks you have a Chrome extension installed that is blocking Google web fonts.
